WEBVTT

00:00.062 --> 00:01.867
Previously on "Blood & Oil"...

00:01.892 --> 00:03.530
Losing the baby is too much.

00:03.555 --> 00:05.265
You're gonna pay for
what you did to my wife!

00:05.300 --> 00:06.633
[Glass shatters]

00:06.668 --> 00:07.934
[Grunting]

00:07.969 --> 00:09.769
We leave him here. We walk away. Oh, God.

00:09.805 --> 00:11.093
Come work for me.

00:11.118 --> 00:12.739
He's taking advantage of your situation

00:12.774 --> 00:13.774
to reel you back in.

00:13.809 --> 00:15.608
There's not one person
willing to back Billy.

00:15.644 --> 00:17.177
There just might be.

00:17.212 --> 00:18.945
Please hold for Annie Briggs.

00:18.970 --> 00:21.381
- I ended it with Hap. 
- Be more convincing.

00:21.416 --> 00:23.016
- You wouldn't dare tell Wick. 
- Yes.

00:23.051 --> 00:25.051
Where were you the night of the rig fire?

00:25.087 --> 00:27.087
Just getting some drinks with some friends.

00:28.123 --> 00:29.123
Damn it, Wick.

00:33.281 --> 00:35.181
- Cody: Just a minute. 
- [Sighs]

00:41.703 --> 00:42.602
Wick.

00:42.898 --> 00:44.070
Hi.

00:44.106 --> 00:46.706
Hi. This is a surprise.

00:46.742 --> 00:48.708
These are for you. I heard
you were doing better.

00:48.744 --> 00:51.411
Thank you. These are beautiful.

00:51.446 --> 00:52.746
[Clears throat]

00:54.049 --> 00:56.082
Um, well, do you want to come in?

00:56.118 --> 00:57.417
No, uh, actually,

00:57.452 --> 00:59.953
I was hoping I could talk to
Billy outside for a second.

00:59.988 --> 01:03.223
Yeah, let's go outside, have a chat.

01:03.258 --> 01:04.691
I'll be one minute, honey.

01:10.332 --> 01:11.798
- Billy: Hey. 
- Wick: It's been three days.

01:11.833 --> 01:13.967
- I haven't heard anything yet.
- That's because Gary's dead, man.

01:14.002 --> 01:15.435
Yeah, but they haven't found the body yet.

01:15.470 --> 01:18.204
He... he's in a ravine somewhere
deep in the woods, okay?

01:18.240 --> 01:20.473
I mean, it could take
weeks to find him, man.

01:20.509 --> 01:22.342
- All right. 
- [Sighs]

01:22.377 --> 01:25.278
And look, even if they do,
Gary was on the run, okay?

01:25.313 --> 01:26.479
He was on drugs. He fell.

01:26.515 --> 01:28.481
And anyone who finds
him is gonna think that,

01:28.517 --> 01:29.517
including the sheriff.

01:32.703 --> 01:33.686
Okay.

01:33.722 --> 01:35.755
Hey, thanks. Look, I was
just checking, you know,

01:35.791 --> 01:38.024
'cause I've been trying to get
Gary off my back for weeks now.

01:38.059 --> 01:39.692
It's just hard to believe
that it could finally be over.

01:39.728 --> 01:41.027
I know you have, okay?

01:41.062 --> 01:43.229
But everything's gonna be okay.

01:43.265 --> 01:44.464
And listen.

01:44.499 --> 01:48.034
There is no way this
will ever come back on us.

01:48.069 --> 01:49.636
Just remember that.

01:57.145 --> 01:58.344
[Panting] Hey, wait up.

01:58.380 --> 01:59.479
[Breathes deeply]

02:02.717 --> 02:04.384
[Inhales deeply]

02:04.886 --> 02:07.420
- [Gasps] Oh, my God! 
- Whoa. Stay back.

02:07.456 --> 02:09.389
No, stop. Wait, what are you doing?

02:13.662 --> 02:14.662
He's alive.

02:17.914 --> 02:23.620
-- Synced and corrected by ChrisKe --
-- www.addic7ed.com --

02:24.706 --> 02:27.707
♪ Oh, well, I'm remembering when ♪

02:27.742 --> 02:30.844
♪ we were so young and innocent ♪

02:30.879 --> 02:32.178
♪ oh, oh ♪

02:33.181 --> 02:35.815
♪ so young and free ♪

02:38.053 --> 02:41.488
♪ the smell of pine on my mind ♪

02:41.523 --> 02:43.099
- ♪ running through some drudges ♪ 
- Billy: What is he doing?

02:43.124 --> 02:44.524
What are you?

02:44.559 --> 02:46.893
♪ Oh, oh ♪

02:46.928 --> 02:49.329
- ♪ on the hi-line ♪
- Emma: Billy, pull over!

02:51.399 --> 02:52.932
Well, what the hell, Clifton?

02:52.968 --> 02:55.168
You auditioning for "Fast
and Furious 8" or something?

02:55.203 --> 02:56.336
Why aren't you answering your phone?

02:56.371 --> 02:57.604
We've been chasing you for over two miles.

02:57.639 --> 02:59.672
Yeah, I can see that.

02:59.708 --> 03:01.474
I mean, what's so important
it couldn't wait, huh?

03:01.510 --> 03:03.576
An opportunity, son.

03:03.612 --> 03:05.703
One that could change your life.

03:08.083 --> 03:09.649
[Sighs]

03:12.414 --> 03:14.703
So, what's so important you 
needed me to come down here?

03:14.728 --> 03:16.421
I didn't need you to come down here.

03:17.472 --> 03:18.671
These people did.

03:22.927 --> 03:23.959
Tip: All yours.

03:24.324 --> 03:25.578
Thank you, sheriff.

03:26.138 --> 03:27.750
Good morning, Mr. Briggs.

03:27.775 --> 03:29.841
I'm Agent Reese. This is Agent Bender.

03:29.977 --> 03:32.546
And we work out of the FBI regional office.

03:34.723 --> 03:36.054
What's this about?

03:36.248 --> 03:37.948
A classified geological report

03:37.973 --> 03:40.641
was stolen from the North
Dakota oil and gas office.

03:42.236 --> 03:46.472
[Clears throat] And, um, I care why?

03:46.758 --> 03:47.924
We believe your father

03:47.960 --> 03:49.826
was the recipient of that document.

03:49.861 --> 03:50.648
[Scoffs]

03:50.673 --> 03:51.772
My father wouldn't jeopardize Briggs Oil

03:51.797 --> 03:53.574
by stealing something like that.

03:54.062 --> 03:55.664
Mm, we think otherwise.

03:55.689 --> 03:58.089
And we were hoping to
enlist your cooperation

03:58.114 --> 04:00.078
into building a case against him.

04:01.707 --> 04:03.473
Well, I think the only cooperation

04:03.508 --> 04:05.342
you're gonna get from me is to recommend

04:05.377 --> 04:08.578
just how far up your ass

04:08.684 --> 04:10.017
you can stick your proposal.

04:10.115 --> 04:15.007
♪

04:15.032 --> 04:16.798
Some parting words of advice.

04:17.084 --> 04:19.689
This conversation stays between us, or...

04:19.725 --> 04:20.875
You might find our office

04:20.899 --> 04:23.033
willing to suddenly help Sheriff Hamilton

04:23.058 --> 04:25.095
in any unresolved cases.

04:25.130 --> 04:28.031
And I bet that if we
were to dig half a second,

04:28.135 --> 04:30.936
we might find something
with your name on it.

04:32.327 --> 04:33.693
Should you reconsider.

04:33.839 --> 04:36.806
♪

04:39.707 --> 04:42.207
Billy: So, what was so urgent?

04:42.232 --> 04:44.866
Bucky Carmichael died last week.

04:44.983 --> 04:47.550
Oh. I'm sorry.

04:47.586 --> 04:50.487
Eh, don't be. The man was a jackass.

04:50.522 --> 04:51.688
The point is

04:51.723 --> 04:55.091
he had a plot of land
right next to McCutching.

04:55.127 --> 04:56.192
And now that he's passed,

04:56.228 --> 04:57.894
his family's eager to put it on the market.

04:58.640 --> 05:00.764
Okay, I'm just gonna stop
you right there, all right?

05:01.398 --> 05:03.700
Listen, guys, I'm taking
a job with Hap today.

05:03.735 --> 05:06.102
I was on my way to accept
it when you pulled me over.

05:06.390 --> 05:07.537
Besides, even if I was interested,

05:07.572 --> 05:08.938
Hap's driven up the mineral rights

05:08.974 --> 05:10.340
for everything around McCutching.

05:10.375 --> 05:11.671
[Scoffs]

05:11.696 --> 05:14.163
Clifton, I know you don't
have that kind of money.

05:14.249 --> 05:16.749
We found a financial backer to stake us.

05:17.312 --> 05:19.349
Someone who's garnered a lot of success

05:19.384 --> 05:22.218
by investing in underdogs
with big aspirations.

05:22.254 --> 05:24.296
Plus she hates Hap as much as we do.

05:26.699 --> 05:28.859
Okay, yeah, what's her name? Who is it?

05:28.994 --> 05:31.179
Her name's Annie Briggs.

05:31.523 --> 05:33.263
Hap's first wife.

05:33.671 --> 05:35.465
Real messy divorce.

05:35.500 --> 05:38.468
Lot of bridges burned, lines drawn.

05:38.503 --> 05:39.736
She's on the hook,

05:39.771 --> 05:41.438
but she wants to meet you

05:41.473 --> 05:43.106
before she'll agree to be our angel.

05:43.141 --> 05:47.243
Face-to-face - in Houston... Today.

05:49.114 --> 05:50.747
She sent her plane.

05:50.782 --> 05:53.883
Now, come on. Hap can wait 24 hours.

05:55.835 --> 05:59.585
What's the harm in giving it one more try?

06:03.028 --> 06:04.327
Hap: Earlier today,

06:04.362 --> 06:07.764
Carla and I were informed by
the oil and gas commissioner

06:08.570 --> 06:10.992
that we're being investigated
by the U.S. government.

06:11.867 --> 06:13.536
For what?

06:13.572 --> 06:15.338
Well, it seems they think

06:15.373 --> 06:18.641
that we got our hands on a
U.S.G.S. Report illegally.

06:18.906 --> 06:21.277
Where would they get that idea?

06:21.313 --> 06:22.412
Ahmed?

06:22.447 --> 06:23.913
He's clean.

06:23.949 --> 06:25.582
I cloned his phone.

06:25.617 --> 06:27.183
[Door opens]

06:27.219 --> 06:28.468
Hey.

06:28.956 --> 06:30.630
I didn't get the memo
about a family meeting.

06:30.655 --> 06:31.721
Close the door, please.

06:33.592 --> 06:34.791
What's going on?

06:34.826 --> 06:37.160
The feds think dad stole a land survey.

06:37.229 --> 06:39.929
[Scoffs] Are you kidding me?

06:41.366 --> 06:43.233
Our taxes pay those morons' salaries.

06:43.268 --> 06:44.501
Well, don't worry.

06:44.536 --> 06:47.303
I've got the best lawyers in
the country punching overtime

06:47.339 --> 06:49.506
to make sure that our asses are covered.

06:49.541 --> 06:50.406
But that doesn't mean

06:50.442 --> 06:51.808
we can't do our part around here.

06:51.843 --> 06:53.076
Everybody's got a job to do.

06:53.111 --> 06:56.179
Lacey, you and A.J. pull the
Briggs Oil personnel file.

06:56.204 --> 06:57.337
What are we looking for?

06:57.443 --> 06:59.076
Vulnerable people with secrets.

06:59.101 --> 07:01.687
The kind the government
can leverage into talking.

07:01.960 --> 07:03.497
What can I do, pops?

07:03.522 --> 07:04.721
You're with me.

07:04.756 --> 07:05.756
Pack a bag.

07:05.791 --> 07:07.223
We're gonna go hit all of our rigs.

07:07.259 --> 07:09.526
We got to make sure all
of our drilling operations

07:09.561 --> 07:11.127
are squeaky clean.

07:11.163 --> 07:12.862
With the government snooping around,

07:12.898 --> 07:14.697
we can't afford to be sloppy right now.

07:14.733 --> 07:16.266
Meet me back here in an hour.

07:16.301 --> 07:17.333
Lacey: Okay.

07:20.172 --> 07:21.871
Relax, baby.

07:21.907 --> 07:23.373
This isn't the first time

07:23.408 --> 07:26.209
that the feds have taken
a run at old Hap Briggs.

07:26.244 --> 07:28.211
Well, unlike the last time,

07:28.246 --> 07:30.513
I hope everyone comes out alive.

07:31.476 --> 07:32.675
Yeah, that'd be nice.

07:35.566 --> 07:37.299
[Door opens]

07:41.163 --> 07:43.797
Hey. Jules, you in here?

07:44.029 --> 07:45.195
Jules: Yeah.

07:45.230 --> 07:47.096
Man, I've had a morning.

07:47.132 --> 07:48.665
Me, too.

07:48.700 --> 07:50.834
Actually, a little bit longer than that.

07:55.273 --> 07:56.840
What's that?

07:56.875 --> 07:57.974
As far as I can tell,

07:58.009 --> 07:59.042
these are the clothes you were wearing

07:59.077 --> 08:00.243
the night of the rig fire.

08:00.582 --> 08:03.000
The night you almost
killed your own father.

08:11.359 --> 08:13.659
Finn: Another double
white meat, extra spicy!

08:13.694 --> 08:15.027
Kess: Two doubles straight out of hell.

08:15.062 --> 08:15.995
There's your change.

08:16.030 --> 08:17.429
All right, who's next?

08:17.465 --> 08:19.565
I'll take a number six, well done,

08:19.600 --> 08:21.900
- special sauce on the side. 
- You got it.

08:22.092 --> 08:23.358
Five even.

08:24.127 --> 08:25.426
Special sauce.

08:31.245 --> 08:33.178
Hey, you enjoy now, brother.

08:35.249 --> 08:37.950
Seems like they can't get enough
of that special sauce, huh?

08:37.985 --> 08:40.653
[Chuckles] All right,
who's next? Talk to me.

08:41.616 --> 08:43.895
Jules, I was angry, okay,

08:43.921 --> 08:45.924
at Hap for cutting me
off from the business,

08:45.960 --> 08:46.925
from my inheritance.

08:46.961 --> 08:48.260
Do you realize what you've done?

08:48.285 --> 08:52.037
- [Scoffs] 
- Theft, attempted murder.

08:52.062 --> 08:53.866
You could go to prison for 20 years, Wick.

08:53.901 --> 08:56.810
No one was supposed to be out
at that rig that night, okay?

08:56.835 --> 08:58.337
Billy and Hap just showed up.

08:58.554 --> 09:00.973
[Scoffs] The fire was an accident, Jules.

09:01.008 --> 09:02.241
What would it do to your father, eh?

09:02.640 --> 09:04.276
If he knew his own son almost killed him.

09:04.311 --> 09:06.304
Don't you think I ask myself that?

09:07.531 --> 09:09.515
I have to live with this
for the rest of my life.

09:10.703 --> 09:12.570
But you want to know
what the craziest part is?

09:13.656 --> 09:15.037
That night changed me.

09:15.062 --> 09:16.334
[Scoffs] It changed me, Jules.

09:16.359 --> 09:17.992
It made me realize who I want to be,

09:18.028 --> 09:20.194
and now Hap is willing to
give me that second chance

09:20.230 --> 09:22.597
- to be a better man. 
- [Chuckles] A better man?

09:22.632 --> 09:24.599
- Yes. 
- [Laughs] That's great.

09:24.634 --> 09:25.767
How, Wick?

09:25.802 --> 09:27.468
By lying to me and everyone else

09:27.504 --> 09:29.137
about what happened that night?

09:32.575 --> 09:33.374
Jules.

09:33.882 --> 09:35.376
Don't. No, come here.

09:35.412 --> 09:37.593
No, come here. Listen.

09:37.881 --> 09:39.547
I love you.

09:40.383 --> 09:42.050
I do. I love you.

09:42.085 --> 09:43.951
And I will... I will do
anything that you ask me to do

09:43.987 --> 09:45.023
if we can just...

09:46.122 --> 09:47.122
[Sighs]

09:47.157 --> 09:48.556
just put this behind us, please,

09:48.591 --> 09:49.591
and start over.

09:51.061 --> 09:52.527
I'm sorry.

09:52.562 --> 09:54.228
Jules.

09:54.264 --> 09:56.397
But there's no starting over.

09:58.134 --> 09:59.343
Not for me.

10:01.750 --> 10:04.250
What? Are you gonna tell the police?
You gonna tell my father?

10:04.275 --> 10:06.409
I don't know what I'm gonna do, Wick...

10:07.956 --> 10:09.489
except tell you to get out.

10:11.000 --> 10:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:21.170 --> 10:24.137
♪

10:26.320 --> 10:28.092
Emma: You ever flown private before?

10:28.117 --> 10:29.455
Oh, yeah.

10:29.490 --> 10:31.187
All the time.

10:31.659 --> 10:32.992
Me neither.

10:37.665 --> 10:39.335
Clifton: Well, good luck to you.

10:39.360 --> 10:42.701
You know, Annie really wants
to get back in the game up here.

10:42.737 --> 10:43.936
It's yours to lose.

10:44.453 --> 10:45.419
Wait, I thought...

10:45.454 --> 10:46.620
I thought you were going with us.

10:46.655 --> 10:47.921
Oh, well, I'd love to,

10:47.946 --> 10:49.929
but, uh, my ticker being what it is,

10:49.954 --> 10:52.984
the docs won't give me
clearance for takeoff.

10:53.079 --> 10:56.714
Oh. Well, uh... Okay, then.

10:56.936 --> 10:58.402
Thanks, Clifton.

11:00.752 --> 11:03.119
Want to see how the 1% roll? Let's do it.

11:06.658 --> 11:07.898
Hap: Okay.

11:08.774 --> 11:10.006
All right.

11:10.031 --> 11:11.601
Well, that's good to know.

11:17.369 --> 11:19.302
Thank you very much.

11:19.327 --> 11:20.659
[Hangs up telephone]

11:24.332 --> 11:25.298
Dad.

11:25.911 --> 11:27.304
Is there a problem?

11:27.916 --> 11:29.179
No.

11:29.493 --> 11:30.148
I was just...

11:30.173 --> 11:33.577
I wanted to say how much I 
appreciate you trusting me enough

11:33.602 --> 11:34.768
to bring me in on this.

11:34.804 --> 11:38.172
Oh, when the going gets tough,

11:38.207 --> 11:39.907
that's when the Briggs circle the wagons.

11:39.942 --> 11:41.546
- It's family first. 
- [Cellphone ringing]

11:41.571 --> 11:43.610
Oh. Hold on.

11:43.646 --> 11:45.289
[Ringing continues]

11:45.314 --> 11:47.062
- I got to take this. 
- [Cellphone beeps]

11:47.087 --> 11:48.210
Yeah.

11:48.235 --> 11:49.235
Hi, Walt.

11:49.984 --> 11:52.619
I could really use a friend today.

11:52.756 --> 11:54.124
Um...

11:55.099 --> 11:56.671
[Sighs] Okay.

11:56.696 --> 11:58.329
Uh, hold on one sec.

11:58.491 --> 11:59.470
Change of plans.

11:59.495 --> 12:00.527
This is the attorneys.

12:00.563 --> 12:02.062
They need to see me right now.

12:02.097 --> 12:05.098
So, I'm gonna need you to
go to Williston on your own.

12:05.134 --> 12:07.717
Okay, well, I mean,
it's... Four hours away.

12:07.742 --> 12:09.236
Why don't I just wait for you?

12:09.271 --> 12:11.138
<i>Because this is</i>

12:11.173 --> 12:14.608
what I need from you right now, son.

12:14.643 --> 12:17.625
Unless you're telling me
that you can't handle it.

12:17.650 --> 12:19.356
No, no. No, I can handle it.

12:19.381 --> 12:20.398
It's fine. I'll do it.

12:20.423 --> 12:21.423
Good.

12:21.448 --> 12:22.780
I knew I could count on you.

12:22.805 --> 12:24.604
All right, the, uh, codes for Williston

12:24.629 --> 12:26.862
are up on Carla's desk. Okay.

12:27.732 --> 12:29.498
All right, um, sit tight,

12:29.523 --> 12:31.256
and I'll, uh, be there as soon as possible.

12:32.948 --> 12:34.080
[Cellphone beeps]

12:34.871 --> 12:36.037
Walt again?

12:36.897 --> 12:37.858
Yeah.

12:38.367 --> 12:39.960
You want some company?

12:39.985 --> 12:41.218
Well, I'd love that,

12:41.403 --> 12:43.770
except that you have to stay on top of

12:43.806 --> 12:45.359
the oil and gas commissioner.

12:45.575 --> 12:46.707
We can't afford to have him

12:46.732 --> 12:48.965
going off the rails right now, now can we?

12:49.253 --> 12:51.621
No, of course not, Hap.

12:53.180 --> 12:54.245
Thatagirl.

12:58.787 --> 13:01.788
♪

13:20.437 --> 13:22.471
Hello, Walt.

13:23.958 --> 13:26.659
So, I really just wanted to thank you

13:26.684 --> 13:28.451
for everything that you did for me.

13:28.476 --> 13:30.643
Thank you. They're beautiful, Cody.

13:30.691 --> 13:32.458
You should call my husband
to give him pointers.

13:32.483 --> 13:35.084
- You have much better taste. 
- [Chuckles]

13:35.109 --> 13:37.643
- How you feeling, honey? 
- Um...

13:37.713 --> 13:39.580
We got a John Doe here.

13:39.605 --> 13:42.439
B.P. is 80 over 50 and he's tachycardiac.

13:42.485 --> 13:43.784
Woman: Let's put him on telemetry in ICU 3.

13:43.809 --> 13:45.342
Woman: Cody?

13:45.568 --> 13:48.735
I-I know who that is.

13:48.760 --> 13:51.060
- Ma'am, ma'am, you need to stay back. 
- No, no, but I know him!

13:51.106 --> 13:53.040
No. No. You need to call the sheriff.

13:53.075 --> 13:54.808
That's the man that attacked me.

13:57.844 --> 14:01.078
<i>. Cortner to labor and delivery.</i>

14:04.751 --> 14:07.151
<i>Man: Medical tech supervisor to ICU.</i>

14:07.186 --> 14:08.619
<i>Medical tech supervisor to ICU.</i>

14:09.687 --> 14:12.068
Uh, is he gonna survive, sheriff?

14:12.093 --> 14:13.559
Doctor's saying he'll be lucky

14:13.584 --> 14:15.050
to make it through the night.

14:17.938 --> 14:19.705
Quite the coincidence, huh?

14:20.250 --> 14:21.406
What is?

14:21.442 --> 14:23.041
Few days after that man attacks you,

14:23.077 --> 14:24.476
he's rolled in here half dead.

14:25.117 --> 14:27.500
But it... it was an accident, right?

14:27.525 --> 14:28.747
I mean, he fell.

14:28.783 --> 14:30.649
That's what the nurse's told me.

14:31.988 --> 14:33.688
Well, either way, we got our man.

14:36.783 --> 14:37.783
Take care.

14:49.236 --> 14:51.603
♪

15:00.320 --> 15:02.420
Ms. Lundegren. Mr. LeFever.

15:02.455 --> 15:04.923
- That's us. 
- Ms. Briggs welcomes you to Houston.

15:04.958 --> 15:07.292
You'll meet her later
tonight at a charity gala.

15:07.327 --> 15:08.526
A charity gala?

15:08.718 --> 15:11.129
We're not exactly dressed for it.

15:11.164 --> 15:12.263
That's not a problem.

15:12.299 --> 15:13.906
Ms. Briggs has already taken care of that.

15:14.094 --> 15:16.327
Ms. Lundegren, you're a size two.

15:17.762 --> 15:19.161
Yes...

15:19.186 --> 15:20.485
[Chuckles]

15:20.510 --> 15:22.610
Whew, Annie Briggs doesn't
mess around, does she?

15:22.776 --> 15:25.310
[Cellphone ringing]

15:25.345 --> 15:27.312
- Just one minute. 
- [Cellphone beeps]

15:27.355 --> 15:29.455
Hey, baby, what's going
on? I was about to call you.

15:29.740 --> 15:30.740
Finally.

15:30.765 --> 15:32.650
I've gone to voicemail like 50 times.

15:32.686 --> 15:34.218
No, I know. I'm sorry, honey.

15:34.254 --> 15:36.621
I've been in and out of
cell range all day, okay?

15:37.015 --> 15:39.687
Uh, how's your first day back with Hap?

15:39.712 --> 15:42.837
Are you showing him that,
uh, Billy LeFever spirit?

15:42.862 --> 15:44.963
[Chuckles] I sure am.

15:44.998 --> 15:46.297
No, it's good. Hap's good.

15:46.333 --> 15:48.166
He's just, uh, had me run errands all day,

15:48.201 --> 15:49.460
keeping me busy, you know?

15:50.203 --> 15:51.203
Are you okay?

15:51.710 --> 15:52.971
Uh, yeah.

15:53.006 --> 15:54.203
Um...

15:54.726 --> 15:57.075
You remember what you said
about the guy who attacked me,

15:57.110 --> 15:59.796
how you said you were gonna
let the police handle it?

16:00.780 --> 16:03.214
I promise you. That guy is long gone.

16:03.249 --> 16:04.914
You need to stop worrying
about him, all right?

16:05.206 --> 16:06.539
Just one minute.

16:06.564 --> 16:08.197
Sorry, I'll be right there.

16:10.857 --> 16:12.290
[Sighs] Cody, did you hear me?

16:12.325 --> 16:15.625
Yeah. Uh...

16:16.162 --> 16:17.528
Look, never mind.

16:17.564 --> 16:19.742
We'll, uh, talk about it when you get home.

16:20.890 --> 16:22.734
Go make Hap another billion, okay?

16:22.769 --> 16:23.901
I will do.

16:23.937 --> 16:25.803
I love you, baby. I'll
talk to you then. Bye.

16:35.144 --> 16:37.377
Well, I'm off to check on the rig.

16:37.602 --> 16:39.235
I was afraid this would happen.

16:40.754 --> 16:41.867
Afraid what would happen?

16:42.171 --> 16:44.022
Hap would give Lacey the real work

16:44.057 --> 16:45.156
and you the grunt work.

16:46.459 --> 16:48.757
Anyone can go loiter around the rigs

16:48.782 --> 16:50.015
and collect papers.

16:50.429 --> 16:52.330
He's the way he's always been.

16:52.365 --> 16:54.054
And I love my sister, so...

16:54.334 --> 16:55.767
Well, he's never gonna change

16:55.802 --> 16:57.835
unless you stand up for yourself, Wick.

16:58.727 --> 17:01.394
Tell him you're ready to
handle some real responsibility.

17:03.940 --> 17:06.874
He wants to be a better
father, then let him prove it.

17:09.804 --> 17:12.150
He has a lunch meeting
at the Tack Room now.

17:12.193 --> 17:14.794
Go remind him you're his son.

17:20.859 --> 17:22.760
I don't know what you're
talking about, Ada.

17:22.796 --> 17:24.762
- You must think I'm stupid... 
- Come on now.

17:24.798 --> 17:26.097
Or blind.

17:26.132 --> 17:27.898
That you can just play me for a fool.

17:27.942 --> 17:29.575
- I'm serious, Kess. 
- I don't want to talk about this.

17:29.602 --> 17:31.169
Don't walk away from me.

17:31.838 --> 17:33.757
Hey, is everything okay?

17:35.608 --> 17:37.296
I found this in Kess' car.

17:37.895 --> 17:38.937
Um...

17:40.031 --> 17:41.230
Indian casino?

17:41.414 --> 17:43.014
People come here to start over.

17:43.281 --> 17:44.554
We are no different.

17:45.318 --> 17:48.486
We had to leave Nigeria
because of Kess' gambling.

17:50.261 --> 17:51.078
Oh.

17:51.758 --> 17:53.057
You never told me.

17:53.093 --> 17:55.703
It's not something you just... Say.

17:57.153 --> 17:59.020
I walked away from my mother,

17:59.045 --> 18:01.585
my sisters, my old friends.

18:02.435 --> 18:04.812
Every day I miss them, and for what?

18:05.305 --> 18:07.105
So he can ruin things here, too?

18:07.140 --> 18:09.073
It's just a matchbook, Ada.

18:09.109 --> 18:10.241
You don't know anything for sure.

18:10.843 --> 18:12.867
I asked him if he was gambling again.

18:13.346 --> 18:15.213
He denied it.

18:15.248 --> 18:16.614
But let's be honest, Cody.

18:16.953 --> 18:19.085
We know what our husbands are capable of.

18:22.807 --> 18:24.328
Yeah.

18:30.887 --> 18:31.953
Hi.

18:33.978 --> 18:35.344
What was so urgent?

18:38.274 --> 18:40.307
I broke things off with Wick today.

18:41.658 --> 18:44.760
And, uh, well, I thought
that you should know.

18:46.092 --> 18:47.092
Why?

18:48.250 --> 18:50.384
Because I couldn't be
with a man that lied to me.

18:53.489 --> 18:57.458
What did Wick lie to you about?

19:02.243 --> 19:03.243
Jules?

19:08.668 --> 19:09.877
It doesn't matter.

19:10.136 --> 19:11.235
[Indistinct conversations]

19:11.271 --> 19:14.272
♪ I don't want to to feel like this ♪

19:14.307 --> 19:17.041
- ♪ I don't wanna let them know ♪ 
- I'm just...

19:17.076 --> 19:20.678
- Glad that you're here. 
- ♪ I will always be alone ♪

19:20.713 --> 19:23.510
♪ I will always be alone ♪

19:23.817 --> 19:26.884
♪ tell me if I hold on to my faith ♪

19:26.920 --> 19:30.221
♪ that's when the miracle awaits ♪

19:30.256 --> 19:33.090
♪ got one foot in the door ♪

19:33.126 --> 19:36.877
♪ or one foot in the grave ♪

19:37.242 --> 19:39.242
♪ misery ♪

19:39.267 --> 19:43.236
♪ always taunting me ♪

19:43.469 --> 19:46.904
♪ won't let me be ♪

19:46.940 --> 19:50.041
♪ dragging me down ♪

19:50.076 --> 19:52.510
- ♪ I can't pay the price ♪ 
- Jules: [Giggles]

19:52.545 --> 19:56.180
♪ Lay down and die ♪

19:56.216 --> 19:59.183
♪ lay down and die ♪

19:59.219 --> 20:05.957
♪ lay down and die ♪

20:08.011 --> 20:10.439
♪ And I'm out all night ♪

20:10.464 --> 20:12.898
♪ shake, shake it, you got that right ♪

20:12.933 --> 20:14.133
♪ I'm so bad ♪

20:14.168 --> 20:17.102
♪ you know I won't be
leaving here alone ♪

20:17.138 --> 20:19.171
♪

20:19.206 --> 20:20.639
♪ I'll flirt with all your friends ♪

20:20.674 --> 20:23.609
Do you have any idea how
much this dress costs?

20:23.644 --> 20:25.544
I could pay off my student loans with it.

20:25.579 --> 20:27.212
Oh.

20:27.248 --> 20:29.114
What? I look ridiculous, right?

20:29.150 --> 20:31.884
No, you look like a
billion-dollar heiress...

20:31.919 --> 20:33.384
Or the bachelorette.

20:33.409 --> 20:34.353
[Chuckles]

20:34.831 --> 20:36.446
You don't look too bad yourself, LeFever.

20:36.471 --> 20:37.696
Thank you.

20:37.725 --> 20:39.391
I guess it's show time.

20:39.680 --> 20:41.012
You ready?

20:41.037 --> 20:42.269
Let's do this.

20:44.498 --> 20:46.131
♪ Ooh, watch out ♪

20:46.167 --> 20:48.767
♪ ooh, watch out ♪

20:48.803 --> 20:51.703
♪

21:04.581 --> 21:06.314
You were right.

21:06.466 --> 21:08.833
So, the feds went straight for Wick, huh?

21:10.127 --> 21:11.890
How'd my boy do?

21:12.377 --> 21:14.927
He told them to shove it
up their federal asses.

21:15.385 --> 21:18.071
[Chuckles] That's my boy.

21:18.099 --> 21:20.899
Wick and I have had our issues in the past,

21:20.935 --> 21:24.036
but when the chips are
down, he's still a Briggs.

21:24.672 --> 21:25.805
Appreciate your tip.

21:25.895 --> 21:28.529
[Chuckles]

21:29.463 --> 21:31.610
Uh, listen.

21:31.645 --> 21:33.679
Not that I don't trust Wick.

21:33.714 --> 21:35.547
<i>I will keep an eye on him.</i>

21:36.659 --> 21:38.703
And if the feds make another run at him...

21:38.728 --> 21:42.730
Hap, you will be my first call.

21:52.729 --> 21:56.401
Emma: Someone should've warned
Annie we're not easily impressed.

21:56.437 --> 21:59.304
I mean, look at this place.

21:59.870 --> 22:01.340
We're a long way from Rock Springs.

22:01.581 --> 22:03.737
The understatement of the century.

22:04.260 --> 22:07.346
Welcome to Houston...
Oil capital of the world.

22:07.792 --> 22:09.689
Ms. Briggs, nice to
meet you. Billy LeFever.

22:09.714 --> 22:11.463
You really didn't have to go
to all this trouble for us.

22:11.488 --> 22:13.288
I mean... think of it as my way of showing

22:13.313 --> 22:15.347
how much I respect your ambition.

22:15.687 --> 22:18.154
Clifton claims you're one to watch, Billy.

22:18.190 --> 22:19.989
A tenacious young wildcatter.

22:20.025 --> 22:21.090
[Chuckles]

22:21.126 --> 22:22.479
And you must be...

22:22.504 --> 22:23.570
Emma Lundegren.

22:23.595 --> 22:25.462
My grandfather's told us so much about you.

22:25.746 --> 22:28.614
Oh, I can only imagine
how that conversation went.

22:29.551 --> 22:31.984
I've always appreciated Clifton's honesty.

22:32.009 --> 22:33.875
It's proven invaluable more than once.

22:33.922 --> 22:36.489
Which is why I was willing
to review your proposal.

22:36.641 --> 22:38.508
- Shall we? 
- Yes.

22:39.315 --> 22:40.995
These are the spec sheets.

22:42.080 --> 22:44.432
I like a man who gets to the point quickly.

22:44.627 --> 22:46.026
So, the property we're looking to buy

22:46.051 --> 22:48.184
is a solid investment,
even if it came up dry,

22:48.220 --> 22:49.619
which trust me, it isn't...

22:49.654 --> 22:50.787
'cause if Hap's nearby,

22:50.822 --> 22:53.122
chances are he knows
something the rest of us don't.

22:53.158 --> 22:54.691
He's gonna hate having to share it with us,

22:54.726 --> 22:55.625
that's for sure.

22:55.660 --> 22:57.594
Sharing's not in Hap's vocabulary

22:57.629 --> 22:59.762
unless it involves other men's wives.

22:59.798 --> 23:01.464
[Laughs]

23:01.499 --> 23:03.721
It's a smart play.

23:03.746 --> 23:05.479
<i>Really smart play.</i>

23:05.704 --> 23:08.037
I hate that I have to pass.

23:08.080 --> 23:09.613
Pass?

23:09.641 --> 23:11.140
Ms. Briggs, we haven't even
given you the pitch yet.

23:11.176 --> 23:13.243
Just let us... I was tempted by your offer.

23:13.278 --> 23:15.311
But I've spent enough of my life

23:15.347 --> 23:17.547
playing war games with Hap Briggs.

23:18.081 --> 23:20.283
But you brought us all this way.

23:20.318 --> 23:21.985
Because unlike my ex-husband,

23:22.020 --> 23:24.287
I'm not afraid to look someone in the eye

23:24.322 --> 23:25.588
when I deliver bad news.

23:26.065 --> 23:28.191
I'd like it if you'd stay for the gala.

23:28.226 --> 23:29.823
It's in my honor.

23:30.236 --> 23:31.468
I find disappointment

23:31.493 --> 23:33.526
washes down easier with champagne.

23:33.698 --> 23:35.198
Enjoy.

23:42.240 --> 23:43.673
$100.

23:50.282 --> 23:51.714
[Engine turns over]

23:51.750 --> 23:53.049
[Sighs]

23:54.586 --> 23:55.886
Hey.

23:56.693 --> 23:58.026
What the hell do you think you're doing?

23:58.256 --> 23:59.122
What do you mean?

23:59.157 --> 24:00.290
Selling our famous chicken.

24:00.325 --> 24:01.424
Don't lie to me.

24:01.459 --> 24:04.060
I saw you, Kess, dealing
drugs right off the truck.

24:04.700 --> 24:06.233
So help me,

24:06.331 --> 24:08.064
if you open your mouth to lie to me...

24:09.501 --> 24:11.334
[Scoffs] It was my only option.

24:11.369 --> 24:13.956
Kess... to save my business, my marriage.

24:14.068 --> 24:15.201
No.

24:15.226 --> 24:16.635
I know you.

24:17.153 --> 24:18.552
You're a good man,

24:18.743 --> 24:19.876
a family man.

24:19.911 --> 24:21.557
You're not a drug dealer.

24:21.669 --> 24:22.634
I don't want to... No.

24:22.677 --> 24:23.976
Don't you see what happens?

24:24.001 --> 24:25.434
People come up here chasing dreams

24:25.684 --> 24:27.583
and then this place turns
them into someone else

24:27.619 --> 24:29.519
until one day you barely
recognize them anymore.

24:30.682 --> 24:32.635
I don't want that to happen to you.

24:33.858 --> 24:35.325
[Sighs]

24:35.360 --> 24:36.926
Tonight I think you need to sit Ada down

24:36.962 --> 24:38.661
and tell her that you've got a great idea.

24:38.784 --> 24:40.229
And what is that?

24:41.143 --> 24:42.620
That you're ready to leave Rock Springs

24:42.645 --> 24:43.643
and go home.

24:48.845 --> 24:50.645
[Inhales deeply]

24:50.891 --> 24:53.725
♪

24:53.750 --> 24:56.351
You think Hap taught Annie
how to screw people over?

24:56.376 --> 24:58.009
Or was it the other way around?

24:58.745 --> 25:00.350
Hard to say.

25:00.385 --> 25:01.951
It's very chicken and egg.

25:01.987 --> 25:03.653
See, the thing I don't get is why?

25:03.688 --> 25:05.855
Why send a plane, you
know, and a tailored tux,

25:05.890 --> 25:07.623
and whatever it is you're wearing...

25:07.659 --> 25:09.058
A $10,000 dress.

25:09.393 --> 25:11.294
If you have no intention of saying yes?

25:11.329 --> 25:13.696
I mean, normal people
don't do stuff like that.

25:13.732 --> 25:15.401
Mm. She's not normal.

25:15.808 --> 25:17.354
She married Hap Briggs.

25:18.117 --> 25:19.216
On purpose.

25:19.241 --> 25:20.874
[Chuckles] Look.

25:21.006 --> 25:22.805
Either one of two things happened today.

25:22.841 --> 25:24.640
Either Annie Briggs

25:24.683 --> 25:26.282
has a Scrooge McDuck pile of money

25:26.311 --> 25:27.343
and nothing better to do

25:27.379 --> 25:29.831
than prank a couple of strangers, or...

25:30.482 --> 25:31.547
She was gonna say "yes,"

25:31.583 --> 25:32.682
and then changed her mind

25:32.717 --> 25:34.604
while we were somewhere
over the Great Plains.

25:39.638 --> 25:41.138
Emma, you're brilliant.

25:41.163 --> 25:43.130
And I think I know
exactly why she changed it.

25:43.155 --> 25:44.565
I'll be right back.

25:44.963 --> 25:47.630
Woman: Oh, what a glorious age, right?

25:47.665 --> 25:49.832
Is there something I
can help you with, Billy?

25:49.857 --> 25:52.201
Look, I know you didn't
fly us all the way down here

25:52.237 --> 25:53.336
just to say no.

25:53.371 --> 25:54.804
I don't think this is the time...

25:54.839 --> 25:57.073
You changed your mind about
going into business with us,

25:57.108 --> 25:58.608
so I have to ask you.

25:58.643 --> 26:00.410
Did Hap scare you away?

26:00.445 --> 26:01.778
Watch yourself, Billy.

26:01.813 --> 26:03.980
The last time a man
talked to me like that...

26:04.015 --> 26:05.768
He used your trust fund as seed money?

26:07.018 --> 26:08.451
Traded on your family's name

26:08.486 --> 26:10.386
until he burned every bridge he crossed

26:10.422 --> 26:12.755
and left you to sweep up the ashes.

26:12.840 --> 26:14.306
[Chuckles]

26:14.331 --> 26:16.198
You're out of your depth, Billy.

26:16.612 --> 26:18.928
Clifton told me what
happened between you and Hap.

26:18.963 --> 26:21.197
It was a genuine love story. It really was.

26:21.232 --> 26:22.999
You started a family, a business.

26:23.034 --> 26:24.834
You know, the real American dream

26:24.869 --> 26:27.065
till one day without any explanation,

26:27.090 --> 26:28.622
it was over...

26:28.981 --> 26:30.213
For him.

26:30.375 --> 26:32.307
I mean, he broke your heart.

26:33.778 --> 26:35.611
And to add insult to injury,

26:35.647 --> 26:37.409
he took your stake in Briggs Oil with him.

26:38.357 --> 26:39.756
[Sighs]

26:39.781 --> 26:41.080
So tell me, what happened?

26:41.252 --> 26:42.552
Did you get cold feet?

26:43.252 --> 26:44.954
Or you just can't live with the thought

26:44.989 --> 26:47.409
of losing to Hap Briggs all over again?

26:48.083 --> 26:51.885
I learned to take the
high road a long time ago.

26:52.061 --> 26:53.894
Maybe you should do the same.

26:54.370 --> 26:55.731
Maybe you're still in love with him

26:55.767 --> 26:57.600
and that's why you changed your mind,

26:57.635 --> 26:59.202
why you won't go up against him,

26:59.237 --> 27:01.571
and that's why you kept his last name

27:01.606 --> 27:03.065
after all these years.

27:05.036 --> 27:07.503
You should've just enjoyed the party.

27:18.523 --> 27:19.987
[Beeps] Carla: Long day?

27:20.458 --> 27:21.624
Yeah.

27:21.659 --> 27:23.526
They're all gonna be long days

27:23.561 --> 27:25.795
until we get Uncle Sam off our backs.

27:25.830 --> 27:27.096
It's late.

27:27.132 --> 27:29.127
Did the lawyers keep you, or just...

27:29.674 --> 27:31.868
No. I stopped by McCutching,

27:31.903 --> 27:33.136
and then I, uh,

27:33.171 --> 27:35.190
covered our bases with the sheriff.

27:35.802 --> 27:36.735
That's it?

27:36.760 --> 27:38.508
You didn't stop anywhere else?

27:38.543 --> 27:40.109
What the hell, Carla?

27:40.370 --> 27:42.768
Since when do you
need a play-by-play?

27:43.292 --> 27:44.157
I'm sorry.

27:44.182 --> 27:45.681
Wick was looking for you earlier,

27:45.706 --> 27:48.006
and I just wondered if he had found you.

27:49.495 --> 27:50.604
No.

27:51.979 --> 27:53.321
I haven't seen him

27:53.346 --> 27:56.651
since I sent him out to
the rigs this morning.

27:56.977 --> 27:58.956
Sorry. I didn't mean to snap.

28:00.104 --> 28:01.070
This is getting to me

28:01.095 --> 28:02.795
a little more than I'm letting on.

28:05.171 --> 28:07.401
Want to join me for a drink by the river?

28:08.483 --> 28:09.849
I'm right behind you.

28:12.010 --> 28:14.343
[Cellphone beeps, ringing]

28:18.677 --> 28:20.677
Hey, Carla, what's up?

28:20.871 --> 28:23.572
I take it you didn't see your father today.

28:23.702 --> 28:24.935
You know what?

28:25.056 --> 28:27.393
After we talked this
morning, I got to thinking.

28:27.849 --> 28:30.183
I was being extremely rash earlier.

28:30.208 --> 28:32.075
I'm never gonna earn dad's respect

28:32.100 --> 28:33.933
by acting like a hothead.

28:33.958 --> 28:35.958
So I decided to drive to Williston,

28:35.983 --> 28:37.082
like he told me to.

28:37.268 --> 28:38.234
And you know what?

28:38.269 --> 28:40.136
From now on, I'm gonna deal with dad

28:40.171 --> 28:41.237
in a more mature way,

28:41.272 --> 28:42.638
the way he would deal with me.

28:42.674 --> 28:44.907
You think that's smart, Wick?

28:45.377 --> 28:47.143
Trust me, Carla.

28:47.436 --> 28:49.385
This is the best way
to deal with my father.

28:51.182 --> 28:53.216
[Cellphone beeps]

28:53.251 --> 28:54.951
Why are we meeting here?

28:54.986 --> 28:57.019
There seems to be a leak
in the sheriff's office.

28:57.526 --> 29:00.089
Don't worry. You're safe.

29:00.124 --> 29:02.237
Okay, so...

29:02.262 --> 29:04.428
This case you're building
against my father,

29:04.453 --> 29:05.619
it's...

29:05.895 --> 29:07.228
It's airtight, right?

29:07.365 --> 29:08.581
Absolutely.

29:08.961 --> 29:10.094
Given his age,

29:10.301 --> 29:11.901
your father's more than likely gonna spend

29:11.936 --> 29:13.236
the rest of his life in prison.

29:17.515 --> 29:18.948
Okay.

29:20.474 --> 29:21.673
I'm in.

29:23.214 --> 29:24.780
What do you need me to do?

29:28.058 --> 29:31.159
We're going back home -  to Nigeria.

29:32.237 --> 29:34.034
Kess wants to leave tonight.

29:35.612 --> 29:36.912
Wow.

29:38.379 --> 29:39.645
I can't believe it.

29:41.534 --> 29:43.000
I already told my family.

29:43.061 --> 29:44.327
They are so excited.

29:44.352 --> 29:45.785
I can barely believe it myself.

29:48.365 --> 29:50.632
Huh. Well, I'm gonna miss you guys.

29:51.370 --> 29:52.690
I will miss you more.

29:53.542 --> 29:54.674
And we are going to pay back

29:54.699 --> 29:55.998
the money you loaned us for the food truck

29:56.044 --> 29:57.243
as soon as we get back on our feet.

29:57.279 --> 29:58.945
And don't try and fight us on this.

29:58.980 --> 30:00.180
[Chuckles]

30:00.215 --> 30:02.573
We owe you and Billy.

30:03.518 --> 30:05.720
Where is Billy? We want to say goodbye.

30:05.745 --> 30:08.288
Oh, long day at his new job.

30:08.323 --> 30:09.323
Hmm.

30:09.432 --> 30:11.332
Then tell him he has a very smart wife.

30:11.357 --> 30:13.090
[Laughs] Perhaps it's time

30:13.115 --> 30:15.082
he found his way back home, eh?

30:16.642 --> 30:18.542
<i>I will tell him just that.</i>

30:19.393 --> 30:20.334
Thank you.

30:33.370 --> 30:34.470
Lacey: Here's a guy.

30:34.495 --> 30:36.628
He's only worked for my dad for a year,

30:36.653 --> 30:38.252
and he has a prior record.

30:44.472 --> 30:45.671
Shoplifting?

30:46.463 --> 30:48.540
Shoplifting is a gateway crime.

30:49.198 --> 30:51.543
The guy took a Snapple
and a pack of cigarettes.

30:51.579 --> 30:53.145
Look, I know I'm reaching,

30:53.385 --> 30:55.414
but sometimes the people we least expect

30:55.449 --> 30:56.948
are the ones that betray us.

30:58.104 --> 31:00.088
- Okay. 
- So... Yeah.

31:00.864 --> 31:03.199
So, this guy has a record

31:03.224 --> 31:05.224
and definitely a lot of inside access.

31:06.227 --> 31:08.327
- Who? 
- Check it out.

31:12.133 --> 31:14.299
Hey, your father said we
have to consider everybody.

31:14.335 --> 31:16.542
Look, my brother may have his flaws,

31:16.804 --> 31:19.771
but he would never turn against his family.

31:19.807 --> 31:22.574
All I'm saying is Wick's got skeletons.

31:22.610 --> 31:24.376
And for all we know, the feds
could have strong-armed him...

31:24.411 --> 31:25.811
Yeah, said the guy

31:25.846 --> 31:27.579
who was strong-armed by the Saudis.

31:27.615 --> 31:29.181
- Oh, all right, yeah, that's it. 
- Yeah.

31:29.216 --> 31:30.716
Yeah, I lied to you about who I was, yes.

31:30.751 --> 31:31.751
Yeah. All right, yeah.

31:31.785 --> 31:33.752
But I'm trying to help your family, here.

31:33.787 --> 31:35.854
All right, I'm tired of
your rich-bitch attitude.

31:36.262 --> 31:37.294
And you know what?

31:37.319 --> 31:39.152
Next time you have something snarky to say,

31:39.177 --> 31:40.610
save it for your Twitter feed.

31:44.098 --> 31:45.297
[Scoffs]

31:47.518 --> 31:48.760
That was kind of hot.

31:54.378 --> 31:55.477
Thanks for today.

31:55.854 --> 31:57.198
I know it didn't quite work out,

31:57.230 --> 31:59.822
but it made my grandpa
happy to see you try.

31:59.850 --> 32:01.471
Yeah, well, what can you do, you know?

32:02.124 --> 32:03.423
So, what's next for you?

32:03.854 --> 32:06.588
There's a research position
opening up at Ohio State.

32:06.624 --> 32:07.549
That's where I was headed

32:07.574 --> 32:10.042
before I got sidetracked by all this.

32:10.067 --> 32:12.368
Oh, I see. What about you?

32:13.081 --> 32:15.401
I'm guessing you're gonna
take that job with Hap?

32:16.290 --> 32:18.357
Oh, yeah, you know, for once in my life,

32:18.382 --> 32:20.316
I'm gonna, uh, stop chasing the dream

32:20.752 --> 32:22.229
and do the responsible thing.

32:25.054 --> 32:26.729
Well, take the job if you have to.

32:27.688 --> 32:28.720
Whatever you do,

32:28.745 --> 32:31.546
don't let Hap Briggs
kill the dreamer in you.

32:34.132 --> 32:35.784
It's what sets you apart.

32:40.606 --> 32:43.073
Yeah, well, I'll do my best.

32:43.098 --> 32:44.143
[Horn honking]

32:45.296 --> 32:48.263
♪

33:09.804 --> 33:11.637
Billy: Hey, babe. [Chuckles]

33:11.662 --> 33:13.112
What are you doing up?

33:14.708 --> 33:15.799
You okay?

33:17.150 --> 33:19.851
Um, I went to the hospital
today to thank the nurses.

33:20.339 --> 33:22.588
Oh, well, that was nice of you.

33:24.425 --> 33:26.057
I wanted to talk to you all day.

33:26.082 --> 33:27.548
[Sighs] I know, babe. I know.

33:27.573 --> 33:29.407
I'm sorry. I wanted to talk to you, too.

33:29.432 --> 33:31.448
I just was in one of those no-cell zones.

33:31.473 --> 33:33.807
And I just, you know, one of those things.

33:34.543 --> 33:37.072
They found the man that attacked me.

33:38.973 --> 33:40.773
He's in the hospital. He's on life support.

33:40.798 --> 33:42.268
They don't know if he's gonna make it.

33:42.293 --> 33:43.010
Wait.

33:43.406 --> 33:44.438
What happened?

33:44.889 --> 33:46.355
The sheriff doesn't know.

33:46.390 --> 33:49.158
Some joggers found him
at the base of a cliff.

33:49.193 --> 33:50.354
Huh.

33:52.382 --> 33:53.776
Did you do something to him?

33:54.765 --> 33:55.998
<i>Did I do something?</i>

33:56.033 --> 33:58.065
Of course I didn't do
anything to him, Cody.

33:58.570 --> 33:59.736
I told you that.

33:59.864 --> 34:00.963
I know what you said.

34:01.182 --> 34:02.463
That's not... That's not what I'm asking.

34:02.488 --> 34:04.054
Wait, are you asking me?

34:04.253 --> 34:05.453
Because it sounds a whole lot more

34:05.478 --> 34:06.744
like you're accusing me of something.

34:06.930 --> 34:08.730
Okay, baby, I'm telling you.

34:09.047 --> 34:10.775
I had nothing to do with that.

34:13.150 --> 34:15.051
[Sighs]

34:15.076 --> 34:16.141
Good.

34:17.513 --> 34:20.284
Because even after what he did to me,

34:21.299 --> 34:23.213
I... Just wouldn't want to inflict
that kind of suffering on anyone,

34:23.237 --> 34:24.612
you know?

34:25.230 --> 34:27.299
Yeah. Me neither.

34:29.985 --> 34:31.251
[Sighs]

34:41.723 --> 34:43.190
I'm gonna go to bed.

34:43.364 --> 34:44.364
Want to come?

34:44.797 --> 34:46.563
Yeah, I'll be there in a minute.

35:01.965 --> 35:03.831
Hey, Wick, it's me.

35:03.856 --> 35:05.222
Listen.

35:05.247 --> 35:07.147
We've got a major problem.

35:12.167 --> 35:13.399
Hey.

35:13.424 --> 35:15.957
So, uh, what did you find out?

35:16.113 --> 35:18.032
They don't expect Gary to live.

35:18.057 --> 35:20.682
- What? 
- Or to ever wake up.

35:20.717 --> 35:22.817
[Scoffs] Are you sure? How do you know?

35:22.853 --> 35:25.020
I have a friend who's a
nurse down at the hospital.

35:25.055 --> 35:26.588
We don't have to worry about it.

35:26.623 --> 35:28.490
Oh, my God.

35:28.525 --> 35:30.559
[Sighs] Man.

35:31.361 --> 35:33.495
- I mean, that's great. 
- [Chuckles]

35:33.764 --> 35:35.864
Well... You know, look,
there was something else

35:35.899 --> 35:37.399
I was gonna talk to you about.

35:39.536 --> 35:42.137
When Cody was in the ICU,
your dad offered me a job.

35:42.398 --> 35:43.964
I'm gonna take it.

35:45.533 --> 35:47.151
Yeah, look, honestly...

35:47.844 --> 35:49.244
I don't know if now is such a good time

35:49.279 --> 35:50.759
to go work for Briggs Oil.

35:50.784 --> 35:51.913
Well, why not?

35:52.932 --> 35:54.249
Just trust me, all right?

35:54.347 --> 35:56.180
Think twice before you take that job.

35:57.120 --> 35:58.320
Yeah.

36:03.135 --> 36:05.694
[Cellphone rings]

36:05.917 --> 36:07.028
[Clears throat] Hello?

36:07.053 --> 36:08.620
Woman: Please hold for Annie Briggs.

36:10.367 --> 36:12.567
♪

36:22.946 --> 36:25.246
I told you I didn't want you here.

36:25.282 --> 36:27.449
It's okay. This will only take a minute.

36:30.420 --> 36:31.940
When I left this morning...

36:33.223 --> 36:35.245
I was so afraid of losing you...

36:37.761 --> 36:40.395
Until I realized I never really
had you in the first place.

36:40.430 --> 36:42.030
What are you talking about, Wick?

36:43.066 --> 36:45.100
How long have you been screwing my father?

36:47.738 --> 36:48.438
What?

36:48.679 --> 36:50.546
How long have you been
screwing my father?

36:51.231 --> 36:52.768
All right, listen, Wick,
you're mixed up, okay?

36:52.793 --> 36:53.964
You don't know what you're saying.

36:53.989 --> 36:55.122
Don't lie to me, Jules!

36:55.147 --> 36:56.947
<i>I saw you two kissing right here.</i>

37:00.054 --> 37:00.986
I can explain.

37:01.011 --> 37:02.310
- Can you? 
- Yeah.

37:02.335 --> 37:04.468
Go ahead. I want to hear it.

37:06.289 --> 37:07.391
Look, the thing with...

37:08.425 --> 37:11.110
The thing with me and
Hap, it's... it's, uh...

37:12.368 --> 37:13.862
I knew him long before I met you, so...

37:13.897 --> 37:16.522
Oh, okay. All right, great.

37:16.547 --> 37:19.567
So what does that make me, then, hmm?

37:19.603 --> 37:20.702
A consolation prize?

37:20.737 --> 37:22.604
No, Wick, of course not. I care about you.

37:22.639 --> 37:23.972
But you love him.

37:29.012 --> 37:30.912
- And he... 
- He loves you, too?

37:31.204 --> 37:32.265
Is that it?

37:34.551 --> 37:35.551
Yeah.

37:35.585 --> 37:36.951
[Chuckles]

37:41.992 --> 37:44.225
You know how many of you there have been?

37:46.235 --> 37:47.435
Do you?

37:47.704 --> 37:48.774
No?

37:50.878 --> 37:53.412
Oil execs, waitresses,

37:53.437 --> 37:55.003
my friends' moms.

37:55.038 --> 37:56.204
[Scoffs]

37:56.740 --> 37:59.407
You know the redhead who manages
the Edson out on Route 29?

37:59.443 --> 38:02.043
- They've been going at it for years. 
- Stop it.

38:02.079 --> 38:04.612
What did he do? Did he buy you a necklace?

38:05.540 --> 38:06.681
Earrings?

38:06.717 --> 38:08.157
No, no.

38:08.631 --> 38:10.831
No, only the special ones get earrings.

38:13.010 --> 38:14.676
Don't you get it?

38:16.120 --> 38:18.187
He was screwing you to get to me.

38:20.207 --> 38:22.774
So congrats, Jules.

38:22.799 --> 38:25.258
Now you know what happens
when you love Hap Briggs.

38:28.608 --> 38:30.508
You get played.

38:33.452 --> 38:35.452
[Door opens]

38:37.650 --> 38:38.650
[Door closes]

38:42.319 --> 38:44.452
Thanks for seeing me on such short notice.

38:44.488 --> 38:45.688
Well, of course.

38:46.089 --> 38:48.289
I'm hoping you're here
to accept the job offer.

38:48.545 --> 38:49.845
And it's for that offer

38:49.870 --> 38:52.070
and for what you did for my wife

38:52.196 --> 38:55.297
that I'll always be grateful. I will.

38:56.166 --> 38:57.368
Okay.

38:58.141 --> 38:59.954
But I can't accept a job.

39:00.971 --> 39:03.338
You see, it just simply comes down to this.

39:03.373 --> 39:06.007
I can't put my future and
the future of my family

39:06.042 --> 39:07.976
in the hands of a man I...

39:08.011 --> 39:09.744
Well, I just can't trust.

39:09.780 --> 39:10.845
[Chuckles]

39:10.881 --> 39:13.014
Well, you could have told
me that over the phone.

39:13.315 --> 39:14.937
I could have.

39:15.218 --> 39:16.851
Yeah, but someone told me recently

39:16.887 --> 39:19.251
that bad news was best delivered in person.

39:20.024 --> 39:21.189
I think you might know her...

39:21.224 --> 39:23.149
She's my new business partner.

39:25.862 --> 39:27.128
Hap Briggs.

39:27.164 --> 39:28.962
Look at you.

39:29.366 --> 39:30.698
Every bit as handsome

39:30.734 --> 39:32.867
as the day you walked out on me.

39:33.208 --> 39:34.474
Well, hello, Annie.

39:35.101 --> 39:37.235
I see you still know
how to make an entrance.

39:37.899 --> 39:41.042
Pity what you did to the house, by the way.

39:41.516 --> 39:43.915
I hear your latest wife was a model.

39:44.969 --> 39:46.881
Clearly she isn't a decorator.

39:47.391 --> 39:49.284
[Laughs]

39:49.467 --> 39:51.664
So, you're backing Billy?

39:53.284 --> 39:57.047
Not so much backing Billy,
as I am coming after you.

39:57.732 --> 40:00.266
Bucky Carmichael's land is mine...

40:00.291 --> 40:01.991
Mine and Billy's.

40:02.020 --> 40:03.887
Paid twice market for it.

40:04.000 --> 40:06.234
But that's what it took to beat out

40:06.269 --> 40:08.369
an aggressive, anonymous bidder.

40:08.405 --> 40:10.271
Guess that makes us neighbors.

40:10.307 --> 40:11.739
[Chuckles]

40:11.775 --> 40:13.241
I taught you well, Annie.

40:13.276 --> 40:16.110
And here I thought I was
the one who taught you.

40:16.146 --> 40:17.846
[Chuckles]

40:17.881 --> 40:20.248
Come on, Billy. We have
a lot of work to do.

40:21.852 --> 40:23.384
Harlan.

40:24.521 --> 40:25.579
Annie.

40:26.023 --> 40:27.589
Mm.

40:32.403 --> 40:33.869
Um, Billy.

40:35.332 --> 40:38.266
You know, we've all heard
all the stories, you know,

40:38.301 --> 40:39.667
about David and Goliath

40:40.063 --> 40:41.936
and how the upstart takes down the king.

40:42.813 --> 40:44.946
Do you know why we like those stories?

40:46.883 --> 40:49.744
Because they're fairy tales.

40:49.779 --> 40:52.665
[Laughs] [Laughs]

40:53.583 --> 40:55.188
So, good luck to you.

40:56.119 --> 40:58.055
'Cause if you're coming after me, son,

40:58.889 --> 41:00.121
you're gonna need it.

41:03.927 --> 41:05.494
Well, may the best man win.

41:05.810 --> 41:07.126
Oh, I will.

41:14.504 --> 41:16.804
[Laughs]

41:16.840 --> 41:19.874
Annie Briggs.

41:19.910 --> 41:22.944
Well, at least it won't be dull.

41:22.979 --> 41:24.812
<i>Woman: Paging Dr. Donaldson.</i>

41:24.848 --> 41:26.481
<i>10 South, room 12.</i>

